                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A well played bard with good gear and blah blah blah will usually twist 5, not four.  More, depending on which songs they're using (some are longer duration).
<br />

<br />
That being said, bards can't:
<br />

<br />
Charm anything of higher level.
<br />
Haste, MR, and manabuff more than their group at a single time.
<br />
Go LD with said effects still working.
<br />

<br />
Though by comparison, enchanters can't:
<br />

<br />
Buff mana/hp regen together. (Nevermind the stacking.)
<br />
Tank like a plate class... bards can tank not *well* per se, but beat us easily.
<br />
Melee for reasonable dps on highly resistant mobs.
<br />
Mez forever in the area of an AE mana drain/tap effect.  (Think Shei in AR.)
<br />
Run while casting.  This IMO is what gives bards the advanatage in so many things that they do; none of their songs are terribly powerful, but infinite channelling skill makes them amazingly useful.
<br />
Heal faster than base regen without worn effects/potions.  I'd lose an awful lot of abilities for this....
<br />
Do any non-magical damage (ice, fire, etc) directly.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Different hammers for different nails, really.  A really well played bard is unbelievably overpowered, but they're so rare that it doesn't come into play often... and there's still things that they just cannot do.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273078&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">~Reebed</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
