                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm not disputing that bards are the most physically demanding class to play, and that by playing a bard you put yourself at risk of carpal tunnel.
<br />

<br />
I'm not disputing that they require a great deal of attentiveness and concentration.
<br />

<br />
I'm not disputing that there are very few bards out there, and even fewer bards with those sort of qualities as players.
<br />

<br />
The thing is, those are shitty ways of balancing a class. If you took a very attentive player and put an enchanter in his hands and a bard in his hands, they should be approximately equal in the level of power they wield (obviously not in the *type* of power they wield, though). But they're not even close.
<br />

<br />
I've already conceded that the simultaneous effect limit and the duration limit (ie, that bards can't do more than a certain number of things at one time, and what they're doing doesn't last all that long). However, I don't think it's as big a deal as people like Thandor make it out to be.
<br />

<br />
On raids, for instance, bard design HELPS their class be more desireable. Five bards on a raid stack a lot better than five enchanters on a raid, because of the sheer variety of their songs and the fact that most of them are group-only. Five enchanters have two buff spells and one debuff to split between them, and then they get to nuke. I can't recall a time when we've turned down bards. If we had 12 bards on a raid, each one would be improving efficiency amazingly; group mana regen, haste, the superior single-group resist buffs, and so on. If we had 12 enchanters...Well, that's a lot of overkill even for the enchanter-intensive events like TRC.
<br />

<br />
Also, the bard 4 song limit isn't as bad as it's cracked up to be. True, the bard can't hold 3 adds mezzed and buff the group too much, but frankly 3 add pulls are a freak occurrence with a bard in the group, who should be pulling anyway. If he DID pull 3, he could mez them all, and the group would live...it would just deal with these 3 mobs more slowly than if an enchanter was in the group. The fact that they're killing every other mob in the zone faster due to the overhaste + DS + better mana regen + bard melee DPS (and no, I'm not saying it's spectacular...but neither is enchanter nuke DPS) will more than make up for that. The only thing that makes enchanters pull ahead is a charm pet...which doesn't work in a lot of areas.
<br />

<br />
Once again, I don't want to play a bard. I do like to see games with balanced playing environments, though.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
