                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The few good bards I know all use programmable gamepads or other gimmicks for maximum efficiency.
<br />
I always refused to use anything but my 105 keyboard and 3button mouse to play, so playing a bard isn't a thing for me.
<br />

<br />
I like bards in my groups. They pull singles pretty fast, bring them in pre-slowed, pre-mez adds etc. Their abilities stack nicely with ours and I don't see the competition (not like sk/pal/war for tanks f.ex. .. you want 1 tank from the 3 classes and the others get left out, but never seen a group that has a bard refuse to invite a chanter). 
<br />
If there's a chanter in the group for Haste and Manaregen, good bards usually switch to other songs (dots or DS or damage absorb .. they have quite a good selection, that's true).
<br />

<br />
Maybe they are overpowered compared to other classes, but apparently the difficulty of playing them balances that out, so that as class, they are balanced.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">~ Retired ~ Hasta la vista, baby  <img src="images/smiles/icon_butt.gif" alt="icon_butt.gif" border="0" /> </span>
<br />
-----BEGIN ENCHANTER CODE BLOCK----- 
<br />
Version: 0.1 
<br />
W65.135 /Vs h+ 4.1khp ft26 g++++ e++++ o T+ !H !t 
<br />
E61.3 /Vs h+ 1.8khp ft8 g+ e+(+) o T+ !H t++
<br />
------END ENCHANTER CODE BLOCK------</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
